Context

I want you to reproduce a single widget from an existing React dashboard, this time as a standalone Angular 21 application using Tailwind CSS v3. The original is a dark-themed energy-trading-style monitoring tool for a portfolio of Solar PV + BESS assets in the Baltic states.

Scope — keep it minimal:

    ❌ No left sidebar
    ❌ No top header / "Technical Dashboard" title
    ✅ Keep the site selector (compact dropdown, top-right)
    ✅ Keep the Solar Production chart card with all its functionality
    ✅ All data must be mocked (no backend, no HTTP)

The page should render just these two things on a dark background: the site selector strip on top, and the Solar Production chart card below it.
Tech stack (strict)

    Angular 21 standalone components, no NgModules. Use the new control-flow syntax (@if, @for, @switch).
    Signals for state (signal, computed, effect).
    Tailwind CSS v3 with HSL CSS variables (no v4).
    ng2-charts + chart.js for charting (Chart.js v4, ng2-charts v6+ which supports standalone). The chart is a mixed bar + line + area composed chart.
    TypeScript strict mode.
    No other UI libraries (no Angular Material, no PrimeNG). Build the dropdowns and toggle group from scratch with Tailwind.

Functional spec — Solar Production widget

The widget is a card with a header (title + subtitle on the left, controls on the right) and a chart body (~280px tall).
Three view modes (toggle group: Intraday / Daily / Monthly)
View	X axis	Data shape	Chart series
Monthly	12 months (Jan–Dec)	Aggregated MWh per month	Stacked bars: toGrid + toBESS (only if site has BESS), plus dashed line for potential
Daily	Days 1..N of selected month	MWh per day	Same series as Monthly
Intraday	96 × 15-min slots HH:MM, but sliced up to current time	MW (instantaneous)	Stacked areas: toGrid + toBESS, dashed area for potential, plus a vertical reference line at "now" labeled NOW HH:MM in red
Header controls (right side, in this order)

    Year select (visible in Monthly + Daily only) — values: 2024, 2025, 2026, 2027. Default 2026.
    Month select (visible in Daily only) — Jan..Dec. Default Mar (index 2).
    Toggle group: Intraday | Daily | Monthly. Default Monthly.

All three controls are compact: ~24px tall, ~10px font, dark secondary background, subtle border.
Header title (dynamic)

    Monthly: Solar Production — 2026
    Daily: Solar Production — Mar 2026
    Intraday: Solar Production — Today 4/17/2026 · LIVE 14:30

Header subtitle

    Intraday: MW (15-min, real-time)
    Otherwise: MWh

Live behavior (Intraday only)

    A setInterval ticks every 15 seconds updating a now signal.
    On each tick, recompute slotsElapsed = floor((H*60+M)/15) + 1 and slice the 96-point array to that length.
    The NOW label snaps to the current 15-min boundary: HH: + floor(minutes/15)*15.
    Clear the interval when the view is not intraday.

