Acceptance criteria

    ng serve shows a dark page with the site selector strip on top and the Solar Production card below — nothing else.
    Toggling Monthly / Daily / Intraday swaps the chart correctly; Year/Month selects appear/disappear per the table above.
    Switching the site to Imavere or Lohu Mets (no BESS) removes the Solar to BESS series from both the chart and any totals.
    In Intraday, the chart truncates at the current 15-min slot and shows a labeled red dashed NOW HH:MM vertical line. It refreshes at least every 15 s.
    Data is deterministic per (year, month) thanks to seededRandom — reloading shows the same bars for the same selection.
    No console errors, no Angular Material, no HTTP, no NgModules.
    Tailwind classes only — no inline style="" except where required by Chart.js options.

